Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Candente, Credicorp, Rio Alto, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-12-06T21:56:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/peru-stocks-alicorp-candente-credicorp-rio-alto-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.5 percent to 20,090.29. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  slid 0.9 percent to 2,563.78.  Industrial and banking stocks dropped after  Standard &
Poor’s  said it may downgrade 15 European nations’ credit
ratings, said  Roberto Flores , head of research at Lima-based
brokerage Inteligo SAB.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, fell 2 percent to $108.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1
PE), the local unit of  Canada ’s third-largest bank, declined 1.8
percent to 40.50 soles.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and
natural gas producer with operations in Peru, dropped 1.8
percent to $1.10.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest
foodstuff maker, slid 1.7 percent to 5.85 soles.  Copper and gold miners slumped after the metals declined in
 New York .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, dropped 5.7 percent
to $1.16.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA  (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
copper and lead mining company, fell 4.3 percent to 90 centimos.
 Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, declined 2 percent to $3.36.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA 
(VOLCABC1 PE), a copper and zinc producer, slid 1.6 percent to
3.05 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  